	<summary>
	1/7/2009--Introduced.<br/>Requires the Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC) to issue regulations requiring that a specified warning label be placed on the packaging of any video game that is rated T (Teen) or higher by the Electronics Software Ratings Board.<br/>
	</summary>
